OTULEAR - The daRk side of OTULEA

Downloading
===========
cd /tmp
git clone git://github.com/nattomi/otulear.git

Configuration
=============
cd otulear
## At the moment there are 3 configuration files:
## * config.R -- user directory and location of alphalist XML. Important!
## * modes.tab -- strings and graphics related to different feedback modes. Optional.
## * cellcolors.tab -- table cell color related to different subjects. Optional  

Installing the R package
========================
## before installing the package it is neccessary to edit at least the config.R file!
emacs -nw otulea/data/config.R
## f.i. 
## usersDir <- "/var/www/otulea/data/user/"
## alphalist <- "/var/www/otulea/data/item/alphalist/alphalist.XML"
## 

R CMD INSTALL otulea -l /usr/local/lib/R/site-library

Installing the develompment version of the web application
==========================================================
We assume that our Apache root folder is /var/www
cp -r otulea/inst/otulea.conf /etc/apache2/conf.d/
(then restart Apache)
mkdir /var/www/otulea
cp -r -T otulea/inst/www /var/www/otulea/
Remember that the 'feedback' subfolder must be writeable
by user www-data

